\f1\b Analysis\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb4 1. Please execute the \cf0 \cb1 \'93figure1.R\'94 first to replicate Figure 1.\cf2 \cb4  \cf0 \cb1 When uploading the main shp and xlsx files, be sure to set your working directory. \cf2 \cb4 \

\f1\b \cf0 \cb1 \

\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb4 2. Run the \'93main_analysis.do\'94 file to replicate Tables 1 and 2 in the main paper. \cf0 \cb1 You should download the electoral and census data from the .dta files and proceed with the analysis. When uploading the main dta files, be sure to replace "$" with your working directory. The tables for the analysis are generated in Excel.\cf2 \cb4 \
\
3. Run the \cf0 \cb1 \'93appendix.do\'94 file to replicate all tables and figures in the appendix.\cf2 \cb4  \cf0 \cb1 You should download the electoral and census data from the .dta files and proceed with the analysis. When uploading the main dta files, be sure to replace "$" with your working directory. The tables for the analysis are generated in Excel. The coefficient results might slightly vary for the spatial models (Table E.5) but will not change any substantial findings (i.e. significance and size). \
\
4. Run the \'93figure_B.1.R\'94 file to replicate Figure B.1 in the appendix. When uploading the main xlsx files, be sure to set your working directory. \
